    "plan_content": "Here is the complete implementation plan for `Bun.INI`:\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n### New Files (3)\n\n1. **`src/interchange/ini.zig`** — A brand-new, self-contained INI parser (no `DotEnv.Loader`, no import of `src/ini.zig`). Exposes `INI.parse(source, log, allocator) !Expr`. Handles:\n   - Sections `[name]` → nested objects via dot-notation splitting\n   - `key = value` pairs with `;`/`#` comment lines\n   - Inline comment stripping, CRLF, quoted strings, boolean/null coercion, `key[]` array notation\n\n2. **`src/bun.js/api/INIObject.zig`** — The JS API object with `parse` (uses TOMLObject's approach: Expr → json_printer → JSValue) and `stringify` (walks JS object, emits `key = value` / `[section]` / `key[] = val`).\n\n3. **`test/js/bun/ini/ini-public-api.test.ts`** — Full test suite for `Bun.INI.parse()` and `Bun.INI.stringify()`.\n\n### Modified Files (6)\n\n4. **`src/interchange.zig`** — Add `pub const ini = @import(\"./interchange/ini.zig\");`\n5. **`src/bun.js/api.zig`** — Add `pub const INIObject = @import(\"./api/INIObject.zig\");`\n6. **`src/bun.js/api/BunObject.zig`** — Add `INI` lazy property, `getINIObject` getter, export in `exportAll()`, and `INIObject` import\n7. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject+exports.h`** — Add `macro(INI)` to `FOR_EACH_GETTER`\n8. **`src/bun.js/bindings/BunObject.cpp`** — Add `INI   BunObject_lazyPropCb_wrap_INI   DontDelete|PropertyCallback` to `@begin bunObjectTable`\n9. **`packages/bun-types/bun.d.ts`** — Add `namespace INI { parse, stringify }` TypeScript types",
